Esh (Êƒ) is a programming friendly shell with a syntax suitable for both
executing shell tasks and writing functions.

Examples:

$ 1+2
3

$ ls
README
esh.rb

$ x = "."
$ ls #{x}
README
esh.rb

$ ls | _.split("\n").size()
3

$ ['a', 'b', 'c'].join("\n")
a
b
c

$ ['a', 'b', 'c'].join("\n") | wc
       2       3       5

